      "content": "# User Authentication Service: Login Endpoint\n\nThis endpoint facilitates secure user authentication for the CloudNexus platform. It accepts credentials to issue a session token, which is required for subsequent API calls.\n\n**Endpoint Details:**\n*   **Method:** `POST`\n*   **URI:** `/v1/auth/login`\n\n**Request Body Parameters:**\n| Parameter | Type | Description | Required |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| `username` | string | The user's unique identifier. | Yes |\n| `password` | string | The user's secret passphrase. | Yes |\n| `mfa_token` | string | Optional multi-factor authentication code. | No |\n\n**Response Codes & Behavior:**\n*   **`200 OK`**: Authentication successful. The response body will contain the `access_token` and `expires_in` metadata.\n*   **`401 Unauthorized`**: Invalid credentials or missing required parameters.\n\n**Service Guarantees:**\nThis endpoint is subject to a strict rate limit of 100 requests per minute per IP address. All requests must include a valid `X-Client-",
